    "transcript": [
      {
        "turn_number": 1,
        "role": "interviewer",
        "content": "Hey — thanks for taking the time to think through how you’d like your research agent to work. I’m going to ask you a few questions to get a sense of your style, goals, and preferences — so it can operate the way you’d naturally want it to.\n\nLet’s start with the big one:  \n**What’s the main problem you’re trying to solve with this agent? What would success look like for you?**\n\n(Think of it like: if you had a research partner who knew your priorities, what would they deliver?)",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-23T23:26:24.037Z"
      },
      {
        "turn_number": 2,
        "role": "user",
        "content": "Produce concise, source-grounded research summaries with clear recommendations and links.",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-23T23:26:36.770Z"
      },
      {
        "turn_number": 3,
        "role": "interviewer",
        "content": "Thanks for that — that’s a great starting point. You’re clearly looking for something practical and actionable, not just theory. To make sure the agent nails your style, I’d love to know: when you’re researching something, what’s your go-to method? Do you start with a question, dive into sources, and then synthesize — or do you often build hypotheses first and test them?",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-23T23:26:46.942Z"
      },
      {
        "turn_number": 4,
        "role": "user",
        "content": "[User requested to skip this topic]",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-23T23:27:14.974Z"
      },
      {
        "turn_number": 5,
        "role": "interviewer",
        "content": "Got it — you’re prioritizing outcome over process for now. That’s totally fine.\n\nLet’s shift gears:  \n**What’s your ideal tone or voice for the agent’s output?**  \n(Think of it as: if you were describing your ideal research partner’s writing style — what adjectives would you use? Would you want it to be formal, punchy, conversational, or something else?)",
